project title- Responsive Web Layout
Description -A responsive web layout is a way of designing web pages so they adapt automatically to different screen sizes and devices—phones, tablets, laptops, and large desktop monitors—without requiring separate versions of the site.

The Core Idea

Instead of setting fixed widths and sizes, responsive layouts use flexible measurements and rules so content can resize, rearrange, and sometimes hide or show elements based on available screen space.

For example:

On a desktop, a page might show:

[Sidebar] [Main Content]
On a phone, the same page might become:[Main Content]
[Sidebar]
